other_tests.findings: Genetic mapping was performed at the International Center for Neuroscience and Rehabilitation.

CBCT identified 13 dental ageneses, including the upper central incisor and several premolars and molars, characterizing oligodontia. CBCT images showed the position of the permanent lower canines displaced buccally and the upper canines displaced lingually, with the single median maxillary central incisor positioned in the midpalatal raphe and showing malformation.
